nodes.text: Zabraki, or Zabrak was the native language of the Zabrak species from Iridonia. Most Zabrak were fluent in both Zabrak language and Basic, being literate in both languages.
Agen Kolar spoke in a "gentle Zabrak baritone", suggesting that that vocal trait was common among the Zabraks.
The word Kaz, as in the name Kaz Lo, meant "clever" or "innovative". The word "Ouc" as in the name "Oucoa" pronounced Oak-oa meant "Brave" or "Fearless one".
